A 23-year-old sickle cell patient at the Ahmadu Bello University Teaching Hospital (ABUTH) in Shika, Kaduna state, Miss Zinatu Sanusi, is pleading with kind-hearted Nigerians to come to her aid to raise a sum of N2.5million to enable undergo bilateral total hip replacement. Zinatu, who is a Level 1 student of ABUTH Nursing School, Zaria and hails from Kaduna state, was admitted at the tertiary medical facility on December 4, 2019 on account of swelling on the left elbow, bilateral hip pains, swelling on the right hemithorax and swelling on the right leg. According to a letter addressed ‘to whom it may concern’ dated March 4, 2020 and signed by Dr. Tijjani Sadiq, a unit consultant at the Department of Trauma and Orthopaedic Surgery of ABUTH, the patient requires bilateral total hip replacement having underwent some medical procedures. Financial donations can be sent to her through FCMB Bank Account No: 5496985012, Account Name: Sunusi Zeenat Abdulqadir and for further enquiries, the patient can be contacted through phone numbers: 08135544573, 09061681163.